Comment Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 12:31 PM By Caitlyn MahlumSports Editor Posted Oct. 16, 2015 at 12:31 PM Sting football has officially came to a close this season after a loss to Redwood Valley last Tuesday night. After a 53-0 loss to BOLD on Friday, October 9, YME was scheduled to play the Redwood Valley Cardinals in the first round of section/district playoffs. YME was the number seven seed while Redwood was the number two seed. Facing a team with a better record, the Sting were 1-7 and the Cardinals were 5-3, the Sting were unable to pull it through and make it to the next round. The final score ended up being 39-15, with the win going to theCardinals. Redwood dominated the scoreboard for the first three quarters. The Cardinals had 14 points earned in both the first and second quarters, with 11 earned in the third. The Sting buzzed to life suddenly in the fourth, scoring 15 points thanks to a 24-yard run by Jordan Odegard and a kick by Logan Thorstad. To bring the score up to 15 for the Sting, Jack Anderson caught a 34-yard pass fromNicholas Linstrom. The fifteen points in the fourth quarter scoring blitz were not enough, however, and the Cardinals took home the win 39-15 against the Sting.
